o University\">Kyoto University<\/a>; as a senior investigator at the UCSF-affiliated <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/J._David_Gladstone_Institutes\" title=\"J. David Gladstone Institutes\" class=\"mw-redirect\">J. David Gladstone Institutes<\/a> in San Francisco, California; and as a professor of anatomy at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_California,_San_Francisco\" title=\"University of California, San Francisco\">University of California, San Francisco<\/a> (UCSF). Yamanaka is also a past president of the International Society for Stem Cell Research (ISSCR).<\/p><p>He received the 2010 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/BBVA_Foundation_Frontiers_of_Knowledge_Award\" title=\"BBVA Foundation Frontiers of Knowledge Award\">BBVA Foundation Frontiers of Knowledge Award<\/a> in Biomedicine category. Also he received the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wolf_Prize_in_Medicine\" title=\"Wolf Prize in Medicine\">Wolf Prize in Medicine<\/a> in 2011 with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Rudolf_Jaenisch\" title=\"Rudolf Jaenisch\">Rudolf Jaenisch<\/a>;<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Shinya_Yamanaka#cite_note-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Millennium_Technology_Prize\" title=\"Millennium Technology Prize\">Millennium Technology Prize<\/a> in 2012 together with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Linus_Torvalds\" title=\"Linus Torvalds\">Linus Torvalds<\/a>. In 2012 he and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Gurdon\" title=\"John Gurdon\">John Gurdon<\/a> were awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_for_Physiology_or_Medicine\" title=\"Nobel Prize for Physiology or Medicine\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Nobel Prize for Physiology or Medicine<\/a> for the discovery that mature cells can be converted to stem cells.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Shinya_Yamanaka#cite_note-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> In 2013 he was awarded the $3 million <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Breakthrough_Prize_in_Life_Sciences\" title=\"Breakthrough Prize in Life Sciences\">Breakthrough Prize in Life Sciences<\/a> for his work.<\/p>","name":"Shinya Yamanaka","place_of_birth":"Higashi\u014dsaka, Osaka , Japan","place_of_death":null,"text":"Shinya Yamanaka , Physiology or Medicine, 2012","year":2012.0}